<div class="heading-green">Do you know ?</div>
•   A single mature tree can absorb carbon dioxide at a rate of 48 lbs/year and release enough oxygen back into the atmosphere to support 2 human beings. <div class="note">Source: McAliney, Mike: Documentation and Information Sources for Land Resources Protection, Trust for Public Land, Sacramento, CA, December, 1993</div><br/> 
•   One acre of trees annually consumes the amount of carbon dioxide equivalent to that produced by driving an average car for 26,000 miles. That same acre of trees also produces enough oxygen for 18 people to breathe for a year. <div class="note">Source: The New York Times</div><br/><br/>

